The paper focuses on image-text matching, which is a problem in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attention mechanism, which is a common technique in natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves learning joint embeddings, which is a common task in information retrieval, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also experiments on popular datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia research, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for a practical application, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
